C) This would produce an upper half arrow pointing to the left, not right.
D) This produces a full arrow pointing left, not an upper half arrow pointing right.

Note: To use this command, you need to include \usetikzlibrary{arrows.meta} in your preamble and be using PGF 3.0 or later.

